Hi Santu,

      The fail method &quot;fails&quot; a test :-).
      For what?, you might question...if we really want some line not to be reached, you might test this using a fail. Just like in:

      public void testMyTestShouldThrowAnException() {
      try {
            obj.doSomethigThatThrowsAnException();
            fail( &quot;If we are at this line the excpetion was not thrown. So this test failed. JUnit must know that.&quot; );
      } catch( AnException ex ) {
            assertTrue( &quot;If we are here, the exception was thrown, the test passed!&quot;, true );
      }

      Hope it helps!

Peter.

